257: ## Recipes
258: 
259: When your agent figures out a workflow, it saves it as a recipe. A recipe is a JSON file with steps and normalized selectors. Sootie's internal Action Cascade automatically handles backend routing (AT/CDP/Vision) across different platforms.
260: 
261: ```json
262: {
263:   "schema_version": 3,
264:   "name": "gmail-send",
265:   "platforms": ["macos", "windows", "linux"],
266:   "params": [
267:     { "name": "to", "type": "string", "required": true },
268:     { "name": "subject", "type": "string", "required": true },
269:     { "name": "body", "type": "string", "required": false }
270:   ],
271:   "steps": [
272:     {
273:       "action": "click",
274:       "target": {
275:         "app": "Chrome",
276:         "window": "Gmail",
277:         "name": "Compose",
278:         "role": "button",
279:         "state": { "visible": true }
280:       }
281:     },
282:     {
283:       "action": "wait",
284:       "target": {
285:         "role": "textfield",
286:         "name": "To"
287:       },
288:       "timeout": 5000
289:     },
290:     {
291:       "action": "type",
292:       "target": {
293:         "role": "textfield",
294:         "name": "To"
295:       },
296:       "text": "${params.to}"
297:     }
298:   ]
299: }
300: ```
301: 
302: - Recipes are just JSON. Read every step before running.
303: - Share with your team. One person learns the workflow, everyone benefits.
